{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896029927,"sessionID":"ses_2845c51e5ffeHW8ywQ2rHowlPW","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba6ea27001t80XzpLIlUIpNx","messageID":"msg_d7ba4d418001puGCLsUdiMSzmy","sessionID":"ses_2845c51e5ffeHW8ywQ2rHowlPW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-0dd0c55e51fc46f8a8aa1bfce0ba6b24","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-038/design.md","content":"# AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) |\n| Module | pkg/workloadmanager |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── server.go           # HTTPServer - manages HTTP lifecycle, graceful shutdown\n├── config.go           # Config - server configuration parameters\n├── router.go           # Router - chi.Router wrapper for route registration\n├── types.go            # Types - error types, response types, interfaces\n├── store.go            # MemoryStore - in-memory sandbox storage with sync.RWMutex\n├── lifecycle.go        # SandboxLifecycleManager - sandbox CRUD operations\n├── garbage_collector.go # GarbageCollector - periodic cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes\n├── k8s_client.go       # K8sClient - Kubernetes client wrapper with informer factory\n├── informers.go        # Informers - informer lifecycle management\n├── defaults.go         # Constants - default timeouts, GVRs, labels\n├── handlers/\n│   ├── handler.go      # HandlerFunc, HandlerFuncAdapter\n│   ├── health.go       # HealthHandler - /healthz, /readyz endpoints\n│   └── sandbox_delete.go # DeletionHandler - DELETE /v1/*/sessions/{sessionId}\n└── middleware/\n    ├── logging.go      # LoggingMiddleware - request logging\n    ├── recovery.go     # RecoveryMiddleware - panic recovery\n    └── cors.go         # CORSMiddleware - CORS headers\n```\n\n### Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\nHTTP Request → Middleware Chain → Router → Handler → LifecycleManager → Store/K8sClient\n                     ↓\n              Error Handling (HandleError)\n                     ↓\n              JSON Response (ErrorResponse/SuccessResponse)\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\nHTTPServer\n    │\n    ├── Router (chi.Router)\n    │       ├── HealthHandler (Register)\n    │       ├── DeletionHandler (Register)\n    │       └── Middleware Chain: Recovery → Logging → CORS\n    │\n    ├── GarbageCollector (background goroutine)\n    │       └── SandboxLifecycleManager\n    │               ├── Store (MemoryStore)\n    │               └── K8sClient (dynamic.Client)\n    │\n    └── Informers (cache sync for Pod informer)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### SandboxInfo (`pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`)\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind               string              // AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Sandbox, SandboxClaim\n    SandboxID          string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n    SandboxNamespace   string              // Kubernetes namespace\n    SandboxName        string              // Kubernetes resource name\n    Name               string              // User-provided name\n    SessionID          string              // Session identifier (key for Store)\n    CreatedAt          time.Time           // Creation timestamp\n    ExpiresAt          time.Time           // Expiration timestamp\n    Status             string              // running, terminating, etc.\n    EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint // Access endpoints\n    UserToken          string              // User authentication token\n    ServiceAccount     string              // Service account name\n    ServiceAccountName string              // Service account name\n    LastActivity       time.Time           // Last activity timestamp (for idle timeout)\n}\n```\n\n#### MemoryStore (`store.go`)\n```go\ntype MemoryStore struct {\n    mu              sync.RWMutex          // Read-write mutex for concurrent access\n    sandboxes       map[string]*types.SandboxInfo  // SessionID → SandboxInfo\n    expirationIndex map[string]time.Time           // SandboxID → ExpiresAt\n}\n```\n\n#### HTTPServer (`server.go`)\n```go\ntype HTTPServer struct {\n    server           *http.Server\n    router           chi.Router\n    config           Config\n    handlers         map[string]Handler\n    logger           Logger\n    stopCh           chan struct{}\n    lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager\n    garbageCollector *GarbageCollector\n    store            Store\n    k8sClient        *K8sClient\n}\n```\n\n#### GarbageCollector (`garbage_collector.go`)\n```go\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n    interval    time.Duration\n    onceTimeout time.Duration\n    stopCh      chan struct{}\n    wg          sync.WaitGroup\n    logger      Logger\n    idleTimeout time.Duration\n    idleMu      sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n\n#### K8sClient (`k8s_client.go`)\n```go\ntype K8sClient struct {\n    dynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n    coreClient      kubernetes.Interface\n    informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    podLister       corev1listers.PodLister\n    podInformer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    scheme          *runtime.Scheme\n}\n```\n\n#### ClientCache (`k8s_client.go`)\n```go\ntype ClientCache struct {\n    mu      sync.RWMutex\n    clients map[string]dynamic.Interface  // key: \"{token}-{namespace}\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types (`types.go`)\n```go\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n    Details any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype ValidationError struct { Field string; Reason string }\ntype NotFoundError struct { Resource string; Name string }\ntype InternalError struct { Err error }\ntype ServiceUnavailableError struct { Dependency string }\ntype ConflictError struct { Resource string; Err error }\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Store Interface\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Logger Interface\n```go\ntype Logger interface {\n    Info(msg string, args ...any)\n    Error(msg string, args ...any)\n}\n```\n\n### Handler Interface\n```go\ntype Handler interface {\n    Register(r chi.Router)\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Path | Method | Handler | Description |\n|------|--------|---------|-------------|\n| `/healthz` | GET | HealthHandler.healthz | Liveness probe |\n| `/readyz` | GET | HealthHandler.readyz | Readiness probe |\n| `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}` | DELETE | DeletionHandler | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n| `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}` | DELETE | DeletionHandler | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n\n### HTTP Response Codes\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Response Code |\n|------------|-------------|---------------|\n| ValidationError | 400 Bad Request | VALIDATION_ERROR |\n| NotFoundError | 404 Not Found | NOT_FOUND |\n| ServiceUnavailableError | 503 Service Unavailable | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE |\n| InternalError | 500 Internal Server Error | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n| ConflictError | 500 Internal Server Error | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Strategy\n\n1. **Error Propagation**: Errors propagate from Store → LifecycleManager → Handler → HandleError\n2. **Error Mapping**: Type switch in `HandleError()` maps Go errors to HTTP status codes\n3. **Logging**: All errors logged via Logger interface before response\n4. **Panic Recovery**: RecoveryMiddleware catches panics, logs, returns HTTP 500\n\n### Error Flow\n```\nHandler → manager.DeleteSandbox()\n    → store.GetSandboxBySessionID() → NotFoundError\n    → k8sClient.DynamicClient().Delete() → apierrors.IsNotFound, IsConflict\n    → handleDeleteError() → NotFoundError→nil, ConflictError→ConflictError, else→InternalError\n    → HandleError() → HTTP Response\n```\n\n### Test Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Expected Behavior |\n|----------|------------|-------------------|\n| Sandbox not found | NotFoundError | HTTP 404, continue deletion |\n| Kubernetes API conflict | ConflictError | HTTP 500, logged |\n| Kubernetes API timeout | InternalError | HTTP 500, logged |\n| Store internal error | InternalError | HTTP 500, logged |\n| Validation failure | ValidationError | HTTP 400 |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Categories\n\n| Category | Files | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| Unit Tests | *_test.go | Test individual functions/methods |\n| Table-Driven Tests | store_test.go, types_test.go | Parameterized test cases |\n| Concurrent Tests | store_test.go, garbage_collector_test.go | Race detection, thread safety |\n| Integration Tests | integration_test.go | E2E HTTP server lifecycle |\n| Benchmark Tests | benchmark_test.go (new) | Performance baselines |\n\n### Test Patterns\n\n#### 1. Table-Driven Tests (Recommended)\n```go\nfunc TestMemoryStore_Operations(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        setup   func(*MemoryStore)\n        action  func(*MemoryStore) error\n        wantErr bool\n        errType error\n    }{\n        {name: \"store_new_sandbox\", ...},\n        {name: \"store_duplicate_session\", ...},\n        {name: \"get_nonexistent\", ...},\n    }\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) { ... })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 2. Mock/Fake Pattern\n```go\ntype mockLogger struct {\n    mu         sync.Mutex\n    infoCalls  []string\n    errorCalls []string\n}\n\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n    l.mu.Lock()\n    defer l.mu.Unlock()\n    l.infoCalls = append(l.infoCalls, msg)\n}\n```\n\n#### 3. Fake Kubernetes Client\n```go\nfunc setupTestK8sClient() *K8sClient {\n    fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n    dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n    informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n    return &K8sClient{\n        dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n        coreClient:      fakeClient,\n        informerFactory: informerFactory,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 4. Concurrent Test Pattern\n```go\nfunc TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T) {\n    store := NewMemoryStore()\n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n    \n    for i := 0; i < 100; i++ {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func(id int) {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            store.StoreSandbox(ctx, &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: fmt.Sprintf(\"session-%d\", id)})\n        }(i)\n    }\n    \n    wg.Wait()\n    assert.Equal(t, 100, store.Size())\n}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Current Coverage | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|------------------|-----------------|\n| MemoryStore | ~70% | ≥85% |\n| SandboxLifecycleManager | ~65% | ≥80% |\n| GarbageCollector | ~60% | ≥80% |\n| HTTPServer | ~50% | ≥75% |\n| Handlers | ~60% | ≥80% |\n| Middleware | ~70% | ≥85% |\n| Types/Error | ~90% | ≥95% |\n| **Overall** | ~65% | **≥80%** |\n\n### Test Execution Commands\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests with race detection\ngo test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Run with coverage\ngo test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Generate coverage report\ngo test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n\n# Run short tests (skip slow tests)\ngo test -short ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Run benchmarks\ngo test -bench=. -benchmem ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n### Existing Test Files\n\n| File | Lines | Test Count | Coverage Focus |\n|------|-------|------------|----------------|\n| store_test.go | 381 | 12 | MemoryStore CRUD, concurrent access |\n| lifecycle_test.go | 353 | 14 | LifecycleManager, deletion, expiration |\n| garbage_collector_test.go | 379 | 10 | GC loop, batch processing, concurrent |\n| server_test.go | 138 | 7 | HTTPServer initialization, routing |\n| types_test.go | 166 | 12 | Error types, HandleError |\n| k8s_client_test.go | 128 | 6 | K8sClient, ClientCache |\n| informers_test.go | - | - | Informer lifecycle |\n| config_test.go | - | - | Config defaults |\n| defaults_test.go | - | - | Constants validation |\n| router_test.go | - | - | Router registration |\n| handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go | 248 | 10 | DeletionHandler, response format |\n| handlers/health_test.go | - | - | Health endpoints |\n| handlers/handler_test.go | - | - | HandlerFunc adapter |\n| middleware/logging_test.go | 123 | 8 | LoggingMiddleware |\n| middleware/recovery_test.go | - | - | RecoveryMiddleware |\n| middleware/cors_test.go | - | - | CORSMiddleware |\n| integration_test.go | 313 | 6 | E2E server lifecycle |\n\n### New Test Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| benchmark_test.go | Performance baselines for MemoryStore, GC, LifecycleManager |\n| fakes/fake_store.go | Configurable Fake Store for complex test scenarios |\n| fakes/fake_k8s_client.go | Fake K8sClient with customizable behavior |\n| mocks/mock_store.go | testify/mock Store for expectations verification |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Go Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| github.com/stretchr/testify | v1.9.0 | Assertions (assert, require), Mock framework |\n| github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 | v5.0.12 | HTTP routing framework |\n| k8s.io/client-go | v0.31.0 | Kubernetes client library |\n| k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake | v0.31.0 | Fake Kubernetes client |\n| k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake | v0.31.0 | Fake dynamic client |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | v0.31.0 | API types, errors (apierrors) |\n| k8s.io/utils | v0.0.0-20240711033017-18e509b52bc8 | ptr.To() utility |\n\n### Test-Specific Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| testing (stdlib) | - | Go test framework |\n| net/http/httptest (stdlib) | - | HTTP test utilities |\n| encoding/json (stdlib) | - | JSON response verification |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### 1. Benchmark Test Design\n\n```go\nfunc BenchmarkMemoryStore_StoreSandbox(b *testing.B) {\n    store := NewMemoryStore()\n    sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SessionID: \"benchmark-session\",\n        ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n    }\n    \n    b.ResetTimer()\n    for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n        sandbox.SessionID = fmt.Sprintf(\"session-%d\", i)\n        store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc BenchmarkMemoryStore_ConcurrentRead(b *testing.B) {\n    store := NewMemoryStore()\n    // Pre-populate with 1000 sandboxes\n    \n    b.RunParallel(func(pb *testing.PB) {\n        for pb.Next() {\n            store.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-500\")\n        }\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Context Cancellation Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSandboxLifecycleManager_DeleteSandbox_ContextCancellation(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    cancel() // Cancel immediately\n    \n    err := manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, \"session-123\")\n    assert.Error(t, err) // Should handle cancelled context gracefully\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Timeout Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContextTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n    gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, time.Minute, 1*time.Nanosecond, logger)\n    \n    // Create many sandboxes to exceed timeout\n    for i := 0; i < 1000; i++ {\n        store.StoreSandbox(ctx, expiredSandbox)\n    }\n    \n    err := gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n    // Should handle timeout gracefully, not panic\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Stop/Start Cycle Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestGarbageCollector_StopStartCycle(t *testing.T) {\n    gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, 100*time.Millisecond, 1*time.Second, logger)\n    \n    gc.Start()\n    time.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n    gc.Stop()\n    \n    // Should be able to start again\n    gc = NewGarbageCollector(manager, 100*time.Millisecond, 1*time.Second, logger)\n    gc.Start()\n    gc.Stop()\n}\n```\n\n### 5. ClientCache Race Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestClientCache_ConcurrentGetOrCreate(t *testing.T) {\n    cache := NewClientCache()\n    config := &rest.Config{Host: \"http://localhost\"}\n    \n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n    for i := 0; i < 100; i++ {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func(id int) {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            client, _ := cache.GetOrCreateClient(\"token\", fmt.Sprintf(\"ns-%d\", id%10), config)\n            assert.NotNil(t, client)\n        }(i)\n    }\n    wg.Wait()\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Graceful Shutdown Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestHTTPServer_GracefulShutdown_SignalHandling(t *testing.T) {\n    s := NewHTTPServer(DefaultConfig(), logger)\n    s.Start()\n    \n    // Simulate SIGTERM\n    syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n    \n    time.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n    \n    // Verify server stopped gracefully\n    select {\n    case <-s.stopCh:\n        // Success\n    case <-time.After(1 * time.Second):\n        t.Error(\"server did not stop after SIGTERM\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Spec: `changes/AR-038/spec.md`\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-038/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-038/proposal.md`\n- Tasks: `changes/AR-038/tasks.md`\n- pkg/workloadmanager directory: `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- client-go library spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- Kubernetes fake client documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\n- testify documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/stretchr/testify\n- Go testing best practices: https://go.dev/blog/table-driven-tests\n- chi router documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/go-chi/chi/v5"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/agentd/main.go\">\nERROR [8:2] \"time\" imported and not used\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field ShutdownTimeout"},{"ra